title: Japan - a History in Art (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Japan. A History in Art
Doubleday & Company | 1964 | ISBN: 0385032404 | English | 302 pages | PDF | 43 MB

An assemblage of Japanese art works unparalleled in publishing history illustrates this story of a great and complex civilization. Shown (much reduced) on the jacket are a few of the 237 plates in the book. All 237 are reproduced from new color photographs taken especially for this book in situ, in museums, and in private collections in Kyoto, Tokyo, Kobe, Atami, Yokohama, Kamakura and elsewhere in Japan, as well as in the famous Japanese collections in Boston and Washington
